{"questionId":"22444248","questionHtml":"<p>Hence find the <strong>exact</strong> value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> for which the area is a maximum.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>setting their derivative to zero&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></em><strong>OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>A</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></strong></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>attempt at finding the root of the graph of their derivative&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/6701bf3c13175c13e663b3d8da3b00e339c5c027.png\" width=\"239\" height=\"193\"></p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>20</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mfrac><mo> </mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>(given that function is a negative quadratic, only stationary point is a maximum)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Do not award the M mark if their derivative is not used to find the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-value. Award at most <strong><em>M1A0</em></strong> if their answer is not given in exact form.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><strong><em>[2 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22444248","referenceCode":"24M.1.SL.TZ2.12d","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Hence find the exact value of x for which the area is a maximum.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.3—Differentiating polynomials, n E Z","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.6—Stationary points, local max and min","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.7—Optimisation"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}